<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85742" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85742">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85742">Forewing length: 25-40 mm, hind-wing length: 21-35 mm. Antenna nearly 3/4 as long as forewing. Gena wide. Crossveins in costal area of both wings each with a dark brown marking. Brownish marking posteriad pterostigma in hind-wings. Poststigmal area generally with two rows of cells. Abdomen short, nearly half as long as hind-wing. Male ectoproct elongated, slightly curved, distally swollened with some stout setae, extending ventrally.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85742" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85742">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85742">China, Cambodia, Nepal, India, Pakistan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
